&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pregnancy Advisory Specialist Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gynaecology Minor Procedures and Outpatient Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dedicated Pregnancy Advisory Specialist Nurse to join the Gynaecology Outpatient Team based at The Women’s and Children’s Hospital at Hull Royal Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work as a member of the Pregnancy Advisory Team to deliver an expert nurse-led pregnancy advisory service to patients from initial consultation to discharge. You must have a positive and caring attitude and be able to establish clear lines of communication with hospital and primary healthcare teams in order to increase knowledge and facilitate a unified approach to patient care. You will be motivated to share new ideas for improving patient care and the service and contribute to the development of evidence based clinical nursing practice in line with current research and guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexibility and teamwork are essential for the role and the demands of this busy and varied department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and/or to arrange an informal visit, please contact Julie Fellowes, Senior Sister on (01482) 607893 or via email at julie.fellowes@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
